  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Regular reporting to financial intelligence units\n- Risk-based approach to monitoring transactions\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. Regulatory Oversight\n- Central banks\n- Financial regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n7. Key Stages Addressed\n- Placement of illegal funds\n- Layering of transactions\n- Integration into legitimate financial system\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
